Text.Value: Leave.
*Time passes. You can practically feel your hairs growing, and your eyes watering from trying to stay awake.*
Will you ever shut up?
My... only... wish...
I... had... so many... nice... conversations... with... the customers...
So... I have... no... regrets...
And... that's... how... I... realised... that... being a... chef... wasn't... for me...
That... we... have... to be... persistent...
Do you have any regrets?
Oh the... conversations... we could... have had...
What were you doing before you died?
I guess... we'll never... find out... now...
Alive... But now... that I'm... dead...
Leave.
*The corpse remains silent. It does not know.*

Text.Value: And that's... how I realised... I wasn't... supposed... to be... a shopkeeper...
But I... don't know... how to... play... an instrument...
Leave.
Don't... leave... yet...
Keep... trying... and trying...
How do I make this stop?
What was your profession?
Then... I... tried... to... specialise... in... fish...
But... they... never... came... back...
Have you always been so talkative?
But... butter... gives me... gas...
I will... have... to... try... even... harder... to be... heard...
Leave.
What was your profession before you tried to be an adventurer?
Shame... the stories... I could... have told...
I have... so much... more... to tell... you...
And... I... met... you...
Don't... you... want... to... know... more...
I... told... them... everything... there was... to know... about... the... produce...
Once... I tried... to be... a shopkeeper...
You... even... encouraged... me...
Why... are... you... leaving... me...
Has anyone ever told you you're really annoying?
It... was... three... years... ago... but... I... remember it... like... yesterday...
Sorry not... to have... met you... properly... when I... was... still alive...
Many... people...
Always... fancied myself... a bit of... a bard...
But... I... try not... to... let it... get... to me...
Nice to... meet... you...
Was... to... make... friends...
Did... I... ever... tell... you... about... that... time... I tried... to be... a chef?
I'm... Naaber...
Did you find your calling?
Isn't it... lovely... to talk... to someone...?
And... trying... and trying...
I... don't... understand... why... everyone... else... isn't... the same... way...
About... my... life?
Maybe... some day...
I... never... understood... why... though...
My... father... learned... from his father... who learned... from his father...
He always... said... if at first... people don't... listen...
Son of... Niiber... son of... Nuuber...
I was... trying... to become...
Wait... we... have... only... just... started... talking...
Descendant... of... Noober...
I've... always... been... upbeat...
*His body longs to rest, but his spirit doesn't stop talking, even as he returns to what one can only hope are the deepest depths of the Hells.*
But... not... today...
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Who are you?
Yes... I want to... be...
*The spell's power wanes - but the spirit refuses to be silent.*
But... I never... made... enough... sales...
And... trying... and... trying...
Ha... ha... us... Noobers... sure do... like... to talk...
An adventurer... but I... couldn't... figure out... what... kind...
I... regret... not... being... your... friend...
First... I tried... to be... a... pastry... chef...
Many... times...

Synopsis: Speak with Dead dialogue for Naaber. Unlike most characters, he will talk to his killer and ignore the "power of the spell waning" limit.
